The paper discusses the development of highly autonomous systems for AUVs, which involves challenges in command and control of multi-objective, multi-vehicle missions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of a natural language interface, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The use of relayed acoustic communications involves the use of different mediums and transmission modes, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the integration of working prototypes with established commercial C2 software, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
